Apple Computer is set to switch from IBM to Intel chips in its Macintosh machines, a move expected to streamline production and lower costs.
CEO Steve Jobs announced the transition at a developer conference, citing Intel's superior processor roadmap.
The switch aims to attract a larger developer community and align Mac prices with competitors.
Apple's decision reflects concerns over IBM's outdated Power PC chip and supply shortages.
By embracing Intel, Apple anticipates improved performance and efficiency in its future products, marking a significant shift in the tech industry landscape.
